{% from "components/ai-label/macro.njk" import aiLabel %}

<h2>Default</h2>
<p>
  {{ aiLabel({ describedBy: "ai-summary-explain" }) }}
  Summary of your recent appointments (auto-generated).
</p>
<p id="ai-summary-explain" style="color: var(--nhsuk-dark-grey); font-size: var(--nhsuk-font-size-16);">
  Generated by our clinical summary model. A clinician reviews all
  summaries before they appear in your record.
</p>

<h2>Custom label</h2>
<p>
  {{ aiLabel({ text: "AI-assisted", describedBy: "ai-triage-explain" }) }}
  Suggested next step: book a follow-up appointment.
</p>
<p id="ai-triage-explain" style="color: var(--nhsuk-dark-grey); font-size: var(--nhsuk-font-size-16);">
  Suggestions come from pattern matching on anonymised similar cases.
</p>

<h2>Explainability pattern</h2>
<p>The <code>describedBy</code> param points at a nearby element
  describing what the AI does, how it was trained, and where to
  learn more. This is the minimum viable transparency pattern: the
  AI presence is flagged, and the explanation is one tab away for
  screen-reader users.</p>
